# Environment Variables

## Required for Production

### Formspree (Contact Form)
```bash
NEXT_PUBLIC_FORMSPREE_ENDPOINT=https://formspree.io/f/YOUR_FORM_ID
```

Get your Formspree endpoint:
1. Go to https://formspree.io/
2. Sign up for free account
3. Create a new form
4. Copy the endpoint URL
5. Add to `.env.local` file

### Analytics (Optional)
Vercel Analytics is automatically enabled when deployed to Vercel.
No configuration needed.

For Plausible Analytics (alternative):
```bash
NEXT_PUBLIC_PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN=sebiche.vercel.app
```

## Development

Create a `.env.local` file in the root directory:

```bash
# Copy this template
cp .env.example .env.local

# Edit with your values
NEXT_PUBLIC_FORMSPREE_ENDPOINT=https://formspree.io/f/YOUR_FORM_ID
```

## Notes

- Never commit `.env.local` to git
- `.env.example` is for documentation only
- Vercel will use environment variables from dashboard
